hopobject.body: Not in at the moment where can you buy testofuel Born in 1843, Howard belonged to the generation of British artists who moved away from the tight Pre-Raphaelite style that prevailed in the 1850s to a looser handling of paint that characterised artists associated with the early aesthetic movement, many of whom showed at the Dudley Gallery in the late 1860s. Largely self-taught, he learned his craft both by imitating established artists and by copying the Old Masters. Though he would always struggle to attain even competence as a painter in oil, in time he became a skilful draughtsman and delightful painter in watercolours.
